# The Beginner's Belief

Most people begin programming believing:

```text id="last003"
Software engineering
=
writing code
```

This belief survives approximately until they build their first real system.

---

# The Intermediate Belief

After building several systems, engineers often believe:

```text id="last004"
Software engineering
=
building systems
```

This belief survives until they attempt to operate those systems.

---

# The Professional Belief

After operating systems, engineers discover:

```text id="last005"
Software engineering
=
operating systems
```

This belief survives until they begin managing organizations.

---

# The Expert Belief

Eventually, experienced engineers realize:

```text id="last006"
Software engineering
=
organizational design
```

Because:

```text id="last007"
Every technical problem
eventually becomes
a people problem.
```

